<h1>Getting Started</h1>
<div class="information">
	<i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></i>
	Once you read these steps, you will be ready to create your very own simulation.
</div>
<ul class="list">
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 1:</span>
		To create your own simulation, click <%= link_to 'here', new_simulation_path, class: 'link', role: 'button' %>
	</li>
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 2:</span>
		Enter your information. In the 'Name' field, enter the name you would like to call your farm. 'Start on' is the day on which you would
		like to begin your farming simulation, in the format YYYY-MM-DD. 'End on' is the end date for your simulation, in the format YYYY-MM-DD.
		Under 'Description', you can enter information about your farm.
	</li>
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 3:</span>
		Select the 'Farm' tab and pick the farm you would like to work with or create your own.
	</li>
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 4:</span>
		Select the 'Weather' tab and pick the weather model you would like to work with or create your own.
	</li>
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 5:</span>
		Select the 'Soil' tab and pick the soil model you would like to work with or create your own.
	</li>
	<li>
		<span class="step">Step 6:</span>
		Save the simulation using the green button with the floppy disc icon at the top, right side of the page.
	</li>
</ul>


